Place @cream cheese{1/2%cup} in a #small bowl{} of warm water to soften.

Preheat a well-oiled #grill{} (or #grill pan{}) to medium-high heat.

Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounces} into 1-inch-thick wedges; place in a large #microwave-safe bowl{}.

Toss with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tablespoons}, @dried rosemary{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Arrange potatoes in a single layer in the center of a large piece of #foil{}. Cinch into a packet and add to grill; grill until potatoes are cooked through, ~{60-90%seconds} per side (grills can vary).

> TIP: If using a grill pan, add microwaved potatoes to hot pan; cook, undisturbed, until grill marks form, 2-3 minutes per side.

While potatoes cook, arrange @shishito peppers{8%ounces} in a single layer in the center of a second large piece of foil. Toss with a drizzle of oil and a big pinch of salt. Cinch into a packet and add to grill (or grill pan); grill until peppers are tender and slightly charred, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

Halve @demi-baguette{1}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Mince @chives{1/4%ounce}.

Brush cut sides of baguette with a drizzle of oil. (If using a grill pan, heat a drizzle of oil over medium-high heat.) Add baguette to grill (or grill pan), cut sides down. Grill until toasted, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Watch carefully to prevent burning!

Meanwhile, in a second large #bowl{}, combine cream cheese, @feta cheese{1%cup}, half the lemon zest, half the chives, half the @garlic powder{2%teaspoons}, 1 TBSP water, 2 tsp @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and juice from two lemon wedges until mostly smooth (2 TBSP water and 4 tsp olive oil for 4 servings). Transfer to a #serving bowl{} and garnish with remaining chives and remaining lemon zest.

Arrange shishito peppers on a #serving platter{}. Serve with lemony feta dip and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Serve right-off-the-grill blistered shishito peppers with creamy lemon-feta dip. Serve with your favorite beverage while you prepare the rest of the meal.

> TIP: Prefer to serve with the main course? Keep peppers in foil packet and refrigerate dip until ready to serve.

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounces} dry with #paper towels{}. Rub with a drizzle of oil and season all over with remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper.

Add steak to grill (if using a grill pan, heat a drizzle of oil over medium-high heat and work in batches if needed); grill to desired doneness, ~{4-8%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat if steak begins to brown too quickly.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Transfer steak to a #cutting board{}. Top each with @butter{1%tablespoon}; let rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

While steak cooks, cut grilled baguette into 1⁄2-inch cubes.

In a third large bowl, combine @arugula{2%ounces}, @grape tomatoes{4%ounces}, croutons, a drizzle of olive oil (large drizzle for 4 servings), and as much @balsamic glaze{5%teaspoons} as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice steak against the grain.

Divide steak, salad, and potatoes between plates. Top salad with @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and serve.